  <para style="h">2 Peter</para>
  <para style="toc1">2 Peter</para>
  <para style="toc2">2 Peter</para>
  <para style="toc3">2 Ptr</para>
  <para style="mt2">The second letter from</para>
  <para style="mt1">Peter</para>
  <para style="is1">Introduction</para>
  <para style="ip">
    <char style="bk">The ikarangeb letter of Pidru</char>, igpeendiye din of believers there to various lungsud of Asya Minur (1 Pidru 1:1, 2 Pidru 3:1). The tuyu din of migsulat here, iyan that pegsupak of work of that migpanulu of not true/correct, and pegsupak of malindit eggimuwen of people naangey ran puun of sika teaching. Purisu imbanasalan din sikandan not egpalintutuu of sika teaching su iyan just egpalintutuuwen the teaching concerning ki the messiah. Keilangan also due igtimul ran of faith ran: good behaviour, katuenan, egtigkel of birth, not egkapelaan egtetahad, egtuman of God, and eggeyinawa of duma.</para>
  <para style="ip">Migpanulu the that people of not kun e eglibed the Messiah tenged su nalugluhayan e, ware kun just due miglibed sikandin. But intabak sika of Pidru of eglibed ded iya the Messiah, but not egkeupian the God egkaparusaan the minsan hentew, su the igkeupii rin eg-inniyug the people of sale dan.</para>
  <para style="iot">Main components of Peter's letter</para>
  <para style="io1">Introduction <char style="ior">1:1-2</char></para>
  <para style="io1">The calling of Christians <char style="ior">1:3-21</char></para>
  <para style="io1">The teachers of not true/correct <char style="ior">2:1-22</char></para>
  <para style="io1">The return of Jesus the messiah <char style="ior">3:1-18</char></para>
  <para style="ie" />
  <para style="rem">This is still a very early look into the unfinished text of the <char style="em">Open English Translation</char> of the Bible. Please double-check the text in advance before using in public.</para>
  <chapter number="1" style="c" sid="2PE 1" />
  <para style="p" />
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="1" style="v" sid="2PE 1:1" />This is Simon Peter=P (Grk: Simeon Petros), a slave and messenger of {Jesus the messiah}=PJesus (Grk: Yesou Christos), writing to those who have faith in the sinlessness of our God and saviour Jesus Christ=PJesus that's just as precious as our faith.</para>
  <para style="p" vid="2PE 1:1">...<verse eid="2PE 1:1" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="2" style="v" sid="2PE 1:2" />May you experience much grace and peace through your knowledge of God=G and Jesus=P our Lord.<verse eid="2PE 1:2" /></para>
  <para style="s1">The calling and peg-alam of God kanta</para>
  <para style="p" />
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="3" style="v" sid="2PE 1:3" />He=PJesus has given us everything necessary for life and godliness through his=PJesus divine power as we know the one who called us to his own glory and moral excellence. <verse eid="2PE 1:3" /><verse number="4" style="v" sid="2PE 1:4" />Through these things, he=PJesus has given us precious and very great promises that you will become participants of the divine nature after escaping the corruption in the world of lust. <verse eid="2PE 1:4" /><verse number="5" style="v" sid="2PE 1:5" />For this same reason, work hard to apply your faith adding moral excellence, and to that excellence add knowledge; <verse eid="2PE 1:5" /><verse number="6" style="v" sid="2PE 1:6" />to that knowledge add self-control; to that self-control add endurance; to that endurance add godliness; <verse eid="2PE 1:6" /><verse number="7" style="v" sid="2PE 1:7" />to that godliness add brotherly concern; and to the brotherly concern add selfless love. <verse eid="2PE 1:7" /><verse number="8" style="v" sid="2PE 1:8" />Because if these things are part of you and continually increasing, your knowledge of our Lord {Jesus Christ}=PJesus won't become useless or unproductive. <verse eid="2PE 1:8" /><verse number="9" style="v" sid="2PE 1:9" />But if these things aren't part of someone, that person is shortsighted as if they've forgotten that prior cleansing of their sins.<verse eid="2PE 1:9" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="10" style="v" sid="2PE 1:10" />So then fellow Christians, work hard to make your calling and election certain—that way you will never fall away— <verse eid="2PE 1:10" /><verse number="11" style="v" sid="2PE 1:11" />and so you will be richly provided entry into the eternal kingdom of our Lord and saviour {Jesus Christ}=PJesus.<verse eid="2PE 1:11" /></para>
  <para style="p" />
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="12" style="v" sid="2PE 1:12" />Therefore I=Peter intend to always remind you about these things, even though you know them and are already established in the truth that you know. <verse eid="2PE 1:12" /><verse number="13" style="v" sid="2PE 1:13" />But I consider it right, as long as I live in this tent, to get you stirred up with a reminder, <verse eid="2PE 1:13" /><verse number="14" style="v" sid="2PE 1:14" />since I know that this tent of mine will soon be left behind as our Lord {Jesus Christ}=PJesus himself told me. <verse eid="2PE 1:14" /><verse number="15" style="v" sid="2PE 1:15" />And I will also make every effort to make sure that you will always remember these things after my departure.<verse eid="2PE 1:15" /></para>
  <para style="p" />
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="16" style="v" sid="2PE 1:16" />We didn't follow cleverly crafted fables, but rather having been eyewitnesses of the majesty of our Lord {Jesus Christ}=PJesus, we made his power and forthcoming return known to you. <verse eid="2PE 1:16" /><verse number="17" style="v" sid="2PE 1:17" /><note caller="+" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">1:17-18: </char><char style="xt" closed="false">Mat 17:1-5; Mrk 9:2-7; Luk 9:28-35.</char></note>Because he received the honour and glory from {God the Father}=G when a voice spoke to him with magnificent glory saying, “This is my son that I dearly love and who has pleased me greatly.” <verse eid="2PE 1:17" /><verse number="18" style="v" sid="2PE 1:18" />Indeed we heard this voice from heaven ourselves as we had been taken with him to the holy mountain.<verse eid="2PE 1:18" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="19" style="v" sid="2PE 1:19" />In addition there are the words of the prophets that were fulfilled which you would do well to pay attention to—like a light that shines in the dark places—until the day dawns and the one who is the morning star rises in your hearts. <verse eid="2PE 1:19" /><verse number="20" style="v" sid="2PE 1:20" />And know this foundational truth: all of the prophecy in Scripture doesn't just come from our own interpretations <verse eid="2PE 1:20" /><verse number="21" style="v" sid="2PE 1:21" />or from the ideas of man, but from God speaking via men being guided by the Holy Spirit.<verse eid="2PE 1:21" /></para>
  <chapter eid="2PE 1" />
  <chapter number="2" style="c" sid="2PE 2" />
  <para style="s1">The teachers of not true/correct</para>
  <para style="p" />
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="1" style="v" sid="2PE 2:1" />But just like there were also false prophets among the people, so also there will be false teachers among you who will sneakily bring in destructive heresies—even denying the Master and thus bringing swift destruction upon themselves. <verse eid="2PE 2:1" /><verse number="2" style="v" sid="2PE 2:2" />Many people will follow their gross immorality causing evil to be spoken of about the true way. <verse eid="2PE 2:2" /><verse number="3" style="v" sid="2PE 2:3" />They will exploit you with greed and made-up words but the judgment of old won't be idle and their destroyer won't be sleeping.<verse eid="2PE 2:3" /></para>
  <para style="p" />
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="4" style="v" sid="2PE 2:4" />Because if God=G didn't spare the angels when they sinned, but chained them in darkness and kept them to be delivered to judgement in due course, <verse eid="2PE 2:4" /><verse number="5" style="v" sid="2PE 2:5" /><note caller="+" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">2:5: </char><char style="xt" closed="false">Gen 6:1–7:24.</char></note> and if he=G didn't spare the ancient world but only preserved the eight including Noah the proclaimer of righteousness when the flood came upon the ungodly world, <verse eid="2PE 2:5" /><verse number="6" style="v" sid="2PE 2:6" /><note caller="+" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">2:6: </char><char style="xt" closed="false">Gen 19:24.</char></note>and if he reduced the cities of Sodom and Gomorrah to ashes by a catastrophe which condemned them to being an example of what the ungodly will become, <verse eid="2PE 2:6" /><verse number="7" style="v" sid="2PE 2:7" /><note caller="+" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">2:7: </char><char style="xt" closed="false">Gen 19:1-16.</char></note>and if he saved the righteous man Lot who was distressed by the gross immorality of the lawless people <verse eid="2PE 2:7" /><verse number="8" style="v" sid="2PE 2:8" />and whose righteous soul was tormented by seeing and hearing their lawlessness day after day, <verse eid="2PE 2:8" /><verse number="9" style="v" sid="2PE 2:9" />then the Lord knows how to rescue godly people from their trials, and knows how to keep the unrighteous people to be punished at the day of judgement, <verse eid="2PE 2:9" /><verse number="10" style="v" sid="2PE 2:10" />especially those who follow their fleshly lusts that defile themselves and despise his Lordship.</para>
  <para style="p" vid="2PE 2:10">...</para>
  <para style="p" vid="2PE 2:10">Those bold, self-willed people don't worry about insulting the glorious ones, <verse eid="2PE 2:10" /><verse number="11" style="v" sid="2PE 2:11" />whereas even angels who are greater in both strength and power don't slander or pass the Lord's judgement on those glorious ones. <verse eid="2PE 2:11" /><verse number="12" style="v" sid="2PE 2:12" />But these men act like unthinking animals that are born to be captured and destroyed when they slander concerning things they know nothing about, and they will bring about their own destruction. <verse eid="2PE 2:12" /><verse number="13" style="v" sid="2PE 2:13" />The harm they did will lead to their own harm as payment as their indulgence in broad daylight. They've become spots and blemishes as they feast together with you yet take joy in their deception. <verse eid="2PE 2:13" /><verse number="14" style="v" sid="2PE 2:14" />Their eyes are full of lust for adultery and never cease to sin, and having trained their hearts in greed they entice unstable people to become their cursed offspring. <verse eid="2PE 2:14" /><verse number="15" style="v" sid="2PE 2:15" /><note caller="+" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">2:15-16: </char><char style="xt" closed="false">Num 22:4-35.</char></note>They have left the right path and gone astray, following the path of Balaam the son of Bosor who loved the wages of unrighteousness, <verse eid="2PE 2:15" /><verse number="16" style="v" sid="2PE 2:16" />but he was scolded for his sin when a normally dumb donkey spoke to him with a man's voice to stop his madness.<verse eid="2PE 2:16" /></para>
  <para style="p" />
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="17" style="v" sid="2PE 2:17" />These men are like waterless fountains and like mists driven by storms, and the gloomy darkness is reserved for them <verse eid="2PE 2:17" /><verse number="18" style="v" sid="2PE 2:18" />because they speak vane and inflated words to entice people to fleshly lusts. Those who have just escaped from the errors of their living <verse eid="2PE 2:18" /><verse number="19" style="v" sid="2PE 2:19" />are promised freedom, but they themselves have become slaves to corruption, because whatever a person has been defeated by is what they become a slave to. <verse eid="2PE 2:19" /><verse number="20" style="v" sid="2PE 2:20" />Because if they have escaped the defilements of the world by their knowledge of our Lord and saviour {Jesus Christ}=PJesus and yet get entangled again, they are defeated and have ended up worse off than at the beginning. <verse eid="2PE 2:20" /><verse number="21" style="v" sid="2PE 2:21" />It would have been better not to have known the way of righteousness, than having known it and to turn back from the holy instruction that was passed on to them. <verse eid="2PE 2:21" /><verse number="22" style="v" sid="2PE 2:22" /><note caller="+" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">2:22: </char><char style="xt" closed="false">Prv 26:11.</char></note>The proverb is correct in what it says and has happened to them: “A dog returns to its own vomit,” and “A sow that's been washed wallows in the mud again.”<verse eid="2PE 2:22" /></para>
  <chapter eid="2PE 2" />
  <chapter number="3" style="c" sid="2PE 3" />
  <para style="s1">The return of Jesus the messiah</para>
  <para style="p" />
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="1" style="v" sid="2PE 3:1" />This is now my second letter to you my friends—both of which were sent as reminders to stir up your minds to sincerely <verse eid="2PE 3:1" /><verse number="2" style="v" sid="2PE 3:2" />remember the words spoken in the past by the holy prophets as well as the instruction of the Lord and saviour that came via your apostles. <verse eid="2PE 3:2" /><verse number="3" style="v" sid="2PE 3:3" /><note caller="+" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">3:3: </char><char style="xt" closed="false">Hud 18.</char></note>Firstly you should know that mockers will come during the last days, scoffing, following their own lusts <verse eid="2PE 3:3" /><verse number="4" style="v" sid="2PE 3:4" />and saying, “What about his promised return? Everything has just continued as usual from the beginning of creation right past the time when the ancestors died. <verse eid="2PE 3:4" /><verse number="5" style="v" sid="2PE 3:5" /><note caller="+" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">3:5: </char><char style="xt" closed="false">Gen 1:6-9.</char></note>But because of their desires, the truth is hidden from them that the universe came into being long ago by God's word and the earth was formed out of water and through water <verse eid="2PE 3:5" /><verse number="6" style="v" sid="2PE 3:6" /><note caller="+" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">3:6: </char><char style="xt" closed="false">Gen 7:11.</char></note>and these same waters deluged the ancient world which then perished. <verse eid="2PE 3:6" /><verse number="7" style="v" sid="2PE 3:7" />But the present universe and the earth have been preserved by that same word to be kept for fire in the day of judgement and destruction of those who are ungodly.<verse eid="2PE 3:7" /></para>
  <para style="p" />
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="8" style="v" sid="2PE 3:8" />
    <note caller="+" style="x">
      <char style="xo" closed="false">3:8: </char>
      <char style="xt" closed="false">Psa 90:4.</char>
    </note>But don't let this one thing escape your attention my dear friends, that one day for us is like a thousand years with the Lord, and a thousand years is like one day. <verse eid="2PE 3:8" /><verse number="9" style="v" sid="2PE 3:9" />The Lord isn't slow in fulfilling his promise as some consider slowness, but is patient toward you—not wanting anyone to perish but rather wanting everyone to come to repentance.<verse eid="2PE 3:9" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="10" style="v" sid="2PE 3:10" />
    <note caller="+" style="x">
      <char style="xo" closed="false">3:10: </char>
      <char style="xt" closed="false">Mat 24:43; Luk 12:39; 1Tis 5:2; Rev 16:15.</char>
    </note>But the day of the Lord will come like a thief, when the universe will suddenly pass away, its components will burn up and be destroyed, and the earth and what happened on it will be examined. <verse eid="2PE 3:10" /><verse number="11" style="v" sid="2PE 3:11" />Since all these things will be destroyed, what kind of people should you be? Holy and godly in conduct, <verse eid="2PE 3:11" /><verse number="12" style="v" sid="2PE 3:12" />waiting for and hastening the coming of the day of God when the universe will be set alight and destroyed and its components will melt as they burn up. <verse eid="2PE 3:12" /><verse number="13" style="v" sid="2PE 3:13" /><note caller="+" style="x"><char style="xo" closed="false">3:13: </char><char style="xt" closed="false">Isa 65:17; 66:22; Rev 21:1.</char></note>But we await a new universe and a new earth filled with righteousness according to his promise.<verse eid="2PE 3:13" /></para>
  <para style="p" />
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="14" style="v" sid="2PE 3:14" />And so dear friends, while you await these events be eager and found to be at peace with him—spotless and blameless. <verse eid="2PE 3:14" /><verse number="15" style="v" sid="2PE 3:15" />And consider the patience of our Lord as leading to salvation as our dear brother Paul wrote to you using the wisdom that has been given to him. <verse eid="2PE 3:15" /><verse number="16" style="v" sid="2PE 3:16" />He speaks in all his letters concerning these things, some of which are hard to understand and which ignorant and unstable people twist just like they twist the other scriptures to their own destruction.<verse eid="2PE 3:16" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="17" style="v" sid="2PE 3:17" />So knowing this in advance dear friends, guard yourselves in case you fall from your own stable position with the same errors as the lawless ones. <verse eid="2PE 3:17" /><verse number="18" style="v" sid="2PE 3:18" />Rather grow in the grace and knowledge of our Lord and saviour Kesus Christ. May the glory be his, both now and through the days of eternity. Amen.<verse eid="2PE 3:18" /></para>
  <chapter eid="2PE 3" />
